> You've likely come across figs baked into desserts, dried and nestled onto cheese platters, or preserved and slathered on toast for breakfast. But today, we're mixing things up by pairing fig jam with tangy balsamic vinegar. The result? A sweet and savory sauce that'll completely transform the juicy pork tenderloin it's drizzled over.

== Roasted Carrots & Brussels Sprouts ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%oz} lengthwise. Strip @thyme{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}.

Toss Brussels sprouts on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, half the chopped thyme, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pork ==

While veggies roast, pat @pork tenderloin{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Transfer to a second baking sheet.

Roast pork on middle rack until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest a few minutes, then thinly slice crosswise.

== Pan Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add onion and remaining chopped thyme. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, @fig jam{1}, and ¼ cup water (½ cup for 4 servings). Simmer until thick and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide Brussels sprouts, carrots, and pork between plates. Drizzle pan sauce over pork and serve.